oard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hey Rosanne!</span><hr size=1> I'm just wondering if we are all not being enough of a 'squeeky' wheel these days and if that is contributing to the lack of attention to Skalds?<br>
<br>
Specifically, what is your perception, as our team lead, of Mythic's attitude towards Skalds.  More specifically what sort of response do you get back from Mythic regarding the monthly reports that you compile on our behalf?<br>
<br>
Is there some sort of NDA that prevents you from relaying any sort of behind the scenes communication with us?<br>
<br>
I realize that there are certainly classes that still have some serious balance issues (probably always will be), but when our monthly report seems to generally consist of mostly bugs related to things that apparently Mythic considers 'balanced' for Skalds, and they time and time again do seemingly nothing to correct it - it certainly does not leave any sort of impression that there is any concern whatsoever about us or our issues.<br>
<br>
I would like to know what we as a community are not doing that you see the other team leads and their communities doing to help instigate some welcome fixes and perhaps even some tweaks to help Skalds out?<br>
<br>
You could easily go through just our realm and evaluate the changes to all the classes, and I can not think of a single class that has been as blatently ignored as us.  Coupled with the recent slaps in the face, ala Paladins combined resistance chants, and the total disregard for Skalds as a Melee class, I am loosing faith daily.<br>
<br>
It appears that Mythic has tagged Skalds as the non-melee group friendly char, but who would you rather have at this point - a Skald or a Shaman?  Shamen are insanely versitile now and undenieably as much if not more desireable now than Skalds.  They can Resist Buff, Rez, Heal, End Regen, Have the best aug buffs around, Damage Add.  Skalds can make you run really fast - but who needs that in PvE combat?  Skalds can do their damage add OR their amazing rest song.  But wait Shaman can do a damage add, end regen, health regen for the whole group (at 50x the skald regen rate) with one cast, crowd control with root (which are very good).  And thats just Shaman.  <br>
<br>
Your the team lead Rosanne - what are we doing wrong? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/29/02 3:43:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I agree</span><hr size=1> I second that.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/urufustb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rufustb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/30/02 10:49:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I agree</span><hr size=1> Good points! <p>I am the Lemon Merchant and you are the Keeper of the Cheese.......</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/upranzer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pranzer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/30/02 7:51:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I agree</span><hr size=1> Skalds dmg add is much better compared to the shammy.  You also need to run to some exp spots <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
